result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Jason A Hensler

records.addlTxt: Status conference on November 30, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Court entered not guilty plea for defendant. Motions due 20 days. Bail continued.
Branch 2

Defendant Jason A Hensler in court, in custody.  Attorney Lili Nelson in court for State of Wisconsin. Court reviews waiver of attorney form with defendant on the record. Defendant representing himself for this hearing. All felony counts found transactionally related. Witness B.L. duly sworn and testifies. Direct exam by state. Venue established. Defendant is identified. Mr. Hensler with cross. Witness excused. Motions made; objection made. Court makes findings and probable cause has been found.
Preliminary hearing on October 13, 2022 at 09:00 am.

Reporter:  Patrick Weishan
 Defn does not qualify for SPD or court-appointed-counsel; time limits have previously been waived; Defn has unable to secure private atty; Ct finds for the purposes of preliminary hearing, the defn has forfeited right to counsel; preliminary hearing to be set; bail continued

Prosecuting attorney Will R Davis in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Jason A Hensler in court.  Court speaks to defendant on his attempts to obtain an attorney, not eligible for SPD, and not eligible for CDP due to being above guidelines.  He is still trying to retain an atty.  CT: what efforts is he making?  He has spoken to a few, some won't take the case.  Court instructs that he should be calling numerous atty's every day.  Court will allow another set over for about 30 days.  He needs to contain a list of the atty's he has contacted, warned he is getting close to waiving right to an attorney for prelim.
Status conference scheduled for September 27, 2022 at 11:00 am.
Br 2 notified defn that his petition for appointment of counsel has been denied by the judge due to his amount of income and assets.
Denying petition for appointment of counsel

03:05 PM Defendant appeared.  Tomas Fernando Valerio appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Court colloquy with defn regarding obtaining counsel. Defn has appealed CDP denial. Notice in hand given to defn. Bail continues.
Status conference on August 18, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Appeal of Eligibility Determination for Appoint of Counsel
Defendant not eligible for court appointed counsel through Dane County - income over established guideline.
Initial Application Denied
